Key Match Events: Ajdin Hrustic had a hand in the opener, which was later called an own goal for a critical deflection off Mehedi Hasan's long-range strike.
Kusini Yengi scored the second goal for Australia with a header from a cross by Jordy Bos.
Nestory Irankunda made his debut for the Socceroos and provided an assist.
Australia maintained a perfect record with five wins and five clean sheets in this qualification round.
Pre-Game Insights: Australia's commanding place at the top of Group I allowed coach Graham Arnold to experiment with the team and introduce new players like Nestory Irankunda.
Australia aimed to overtake South Korea in the FIFA world rankings to secure a spot in pot one for the next qualifying round.
Post-Match Reflections: Graham Arnold expressed satisfaction with the team's performance and highlighted the challenging humid conditions in Dhaka.
Nestory Irankunda reflected on his debut, expressing pride and acknowledging the tough conditions.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The pitch conditions in Dhaka were challenging, with the surface deteriorating due to the humid and hot weather.
Australia's victory puts them in a strong position to be placed in the more favorable 'pot one' for the next qualifying round.
